<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF86FFF20D189FBB5C8B" blockId="7.[113,649,1648,1699]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">DISTRIBUTION. — Sud de l’Horombe, de Betroka à Benenitra, jusqu’à Jangany au nord et Beraketa au sud.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36453E14313FF88FD260BB19C505E22" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="230" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF86FD260BB19E075AD8" blockId="7.[674,1210,216,591]" box="[677,821,216,242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF86FD260B9E9E9A5867" blockId="7.[674,1210,216,591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">
Plante acaule, rejetant et poussant en touffes de 5-15 individus. Rosette ouverte de 12-20 feuilles, triangulaires sub-arrondies à allongées, 10 × 
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FB000A5E998B5B79" box="[1155,1209,311,337]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="cm" value="7.0">7 cm</quantity>
à 26 × 
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FD770A3F9E1D5B59" box="[756,815,342,369]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
, parfois tachetées de blanc, à épines plus ou moins distantes. Inflorescence 
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FBCB0A1F99875BB9" box="[1096,1205,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="cm" value="50.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="40.0">40-60 cm</quantity>
, simple ou à 1-2 ramifications. Grandes bractées blanches, scarieuses, à 4-5 nervures marron, 12 × 
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FD260ABC9FDB5BD8" box="[677,745,469,496]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Périanthe droit, mais présentant un renflement à la base, de couleur rose, 25 × 
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FB970A9C99645827" box="[1044,1110,501,528]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. Anthères atteignant la limite du périanthe, stigmate finalement exsert de 
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FCCA095D9E975867" box="[841,933,564,591]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF86FD26091D9FDC58A4" blockId="7.[674,1212,628,1700]" box="[677,750,628,654]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF86FD2609FA9EC15E02" blockId="7.[674,1212,628,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">
Il est à noter, en plus de la différence des bractées bien visible sur les échantillons secs, une autre différence nette entre 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCD609BA9EDE58C5" authorityName="Castillon" authorityYear="2014" box="[853,1004,723,749]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="horombensis" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCD609BA9EDE58C5" box="[853,1004,723,749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. horombensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23961034313FF86FC7209BA996958C5" box="[1009,1115,723,749]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FBF409BA9E285924" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deltoideodonta">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FBF409BA9E285924" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. deltoideodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mais que l’on ne peut voir que sur les plantes vivantes: les fleurs de 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FC54087B99B55904" box="[983,1159,786,812]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deltoideodonta">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FC54087B99B55904" box="[983,1159,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. deltoideodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sont plus grandes (
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FCB7085B9EB45964" box="[820,902,818,844]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
), moins larges et plus arquées (
<figureCitation id="13451CEF4313FF86FD2808389FCB5944" box="[683,761,849,876]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[113,124,1657,1675]" captionTargetBox="[113,1209,215,1629]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[112,662,779,1347]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 2. — Aloe deltoideodonta Baker (synonyme de Aloe madecassa H. Perrier): A, petite forme près d’Arivonimamo, avril 2010; B, près de Behenjy, juin 2006; C, détail de l’inflorescence. Photos J.-P. Castillon." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208568" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208568/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">Fig.2C</figureCitation>
), les fleurs de 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FC04083B992E5943" authorityName="Castillon" authorityYear="2014" box="[903,1052,849,876]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="horombensis" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FC04083B992E5943" box="[903,1052,849,876]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. horombensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23961034313FF86FBA3083B99BB5944" box="[1056,1161,850,876]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
sont plus courtes (
<quantity id="4C86AD8F4313FF86FCA708189E4159A4" box="[804,883,881,908]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
),plus larges,droites et présentent un renflement plus prononcé à la base du périanthe (comme chez 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCB508D89EEC59E2" authority="All." authorityName="All." box="[822,990,944,971]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCB508D89E8059E2" box="[822,946,944,971]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. maculata</emphasis>
All.
</taxonomicName>
et les 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FB9E08D9997A59E2" box="[1053,1096,944,970]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FB9E08D9997A59E2" box="[1053,1096,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">Aloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
du groupe sud-africain 
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCA708B89E5259C2" box="[804,864,977,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">Pictae</emphasis>
, mais ce renflement, même s’il est nettement visible, est cependant bien moins marqué chez 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FD590F799E435E01" authorityName="Castillon" authorityYear="2014" box="[730,881,1039,1066]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="horombensis" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FD590F799E435E01" box="[730,881,1039,1066]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. horombensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23961034313FF86FCFB0F799EDA5E02" box="[888,1000,1040,1066]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF86FD380F599E4E5F0F" blockId="7.[674,1212,628,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">
Les variétés 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCC70F469E9A5E61" box="[836,936,1071,1097]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevifolia">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCC70F469E9A5E61" box="[836,936,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">brevifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FC4C0F46998B5E61" authority="de Perrier" authorityName="de Perrier" box="[975,1209,1071,1097]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FC4C0F4699715E61" box="[975,1091,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">intermedia</emphasis>
de Perrier
</taxonomicName>
n’ont entre elles comme différences que la taille des feuilles (et les taches blanches que peuvent avoir les feuilles de la variété 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FC5C0FE799735E80" box="[991,1089,1166,1192]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevifolia">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FC5C0FE799735E80" box="[991,1089,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">brevifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), mais l’on trouve souvent côte à côte des plantes adultes de toute taille, avec ou sans taches sur les feuilles. Un regroupement de ces deux variétés me semble donc indispensable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1006A4313FF88FD380E449CAB5AD8" blockId="7.[674,1212,628,1700]" lastBlockId="9.[111,647,216,1034]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="230" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">
Vers l’ouest, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCBD0E449EE75F6F" authorityName="Castillon" authorityYear="2014" box="[830,981,1325,1351]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="horombensis" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCBD0E449EE75F6F" box="[830,981,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. horombensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23961034313FF86FC580E4499745F6F" box="[987,1094,1325,1351]" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
cède peu à peu la place à 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCB00E2499AF5F4F" authority="Reynolds (Ranohira)" box="[819,1181,1356,1383]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imalotensis">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCB00E249E8F5F4E" box="[819,957,1356,1383]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. imalotensis</emphasis>
Reynolds (Ranohira)
</taxonomicName>
, et à sa variété 
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FC9A0E059E965FAE" box="[793,932,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">longeracemosa</emphasis>
J.-B. Castillon (Benenitra, Bezaha). La limite morphologique entre ces espèces est très floue (
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCAE0EC59E815FED" box="[813,947,1451,1478]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imalotensis">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCAE0EC59E815FED" box="[813,947,1451,1478]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. imalotensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est une plante plus grosse, aux feuilles plus arrondies,aux marges cartilagineuses continues),la limite géographique tout aussi imprécise peut être approchée par la lisière est de la chaine de l’Isalo. Cette impossibilité à établir des limites précises tendrait à me faire partager le point de vue de Perrier qui ne considérait 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FC2D0D03990B5CAB" box="[942,1081,1641,1668]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="imalotensis">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FC2D0D03990B5CAB" box="[942,1081,1641,1668]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. imalotensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
que comme une autre variété de 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE94313FF86FCEC0DE099855C8C" authority="(sensu Perrier)" baseAuthorityName="Perrier" box="[879,1207,1673,1700]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="228" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deltoideodonta">
<emphasis id="B90ADC784313FF86FCEC0DE0992E5C8B" box="[879,1052,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="228">A. deltoideodonta</emphasis>
(sensu Perrier)
</taxonomicName>
. LES PLANTES PLUS AU NORD
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0150E2431CFF89FFF20D109FC35C8A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5208570" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5208570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5208570/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="229" startId="8.[113,124,1657,1675]" targetBox="[113,1209,215,1629]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8BC1006A431CFF89FFF20D109FC35C8A" blockId="8.[113,1210,1657,1698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">
FIG. 3. — 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE9431CFF89FF420D109C645CA3" authorityName="Castillon" authorityYear="2014" box="[193,342,1657,1675]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="229" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="horombensis">
<emphasis id="B90ADC78431CFF89FF420D109C645CA3" box="[193,342,1657,1675]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">Aloe horombensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J.-P. Castillon, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2396103431CFF89FE540D109F195CA3" box="[471,555,1657,1675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonyme de 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7BE9431CFF89FD2B0D10992A5CA3" authority="H. Perrier" authorityName="H. Perrier" box="[680,1048,1657,1675]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asphodelaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="229" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="deltoideodonta" variety="brevifolia">
<emphasis id="B90ADC78431CFF89FD2B0D109E625CA3" box="[680,848,1657,1675]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">Aloe deltoideodonta</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B90ADC78431CFF89FCF40D109EF35CA3" box="[887,961,1657,1675]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">brevifolia</emphasis>
H. Perrier
</taxonomicName>
): 
<emphasis id="B90ADC78431CFF89FBA70D1099035CA3" bold="true" box="[1060,1073,1657,1675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">A</emphasis>
, forme à feuilles tachetées, Jangany; 
<emphasis id="B90ADC78431CFF89FE9D0DF99C195C8A" bold="true" box="[286,299,1680,1698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="229">B</emphasis>
, en fleurs, à Betroka, juin 2012. Photos J.-P. Castillon.
</paragraph>
